    "details": {
      "biography": "<p>As large as a small cow, the &ldquo;bull pig&rdquo; is a thickskinned, long-tusked breed of porker bred for survival in the dangerous ranges of the Latter Earth. When kept by brave and capable swineherds it can be relatively safely domesticated, but wild bull pigs are as savage and ill-tempered as any boar. Some nations and exceptionally brave tribals even train them for use as battle mounts, though their habit of blind charging is difficult to control.</p>",
